Troops of Special Army Super Camp 4, Faskari, operating under Exercise Sahel Sanity have eliminated 46 bandits in an encounter at Yar Gamji
town in the Batsari local government area of Katsina State
The Coordinator, Defence Media Operations, Major General John Enenche,
in a statement on yesterday, said the encounter took place on July 6,
following a distress call from the community. Major General Enenche said the troops conducted the operation shortly
after their induction into operation by the Chief of Army Staff, Tukur
Buratai, during the 2020 Nigerian Army Day Celebration. According to him, the troops engaged the criminals and successfully
neutralised 46
bandits in the encounter while others escaped with gunshot wounds. Enenche revealed that the troops are presently in exploitation phase
and have dominated the general area with aggressive patrols. The general public is enjoined to disregard news making the rounds in
some online media giving unsubstantiated and false information on the
incident. To this effect, the  Military enjoined the  general public to
disregard news making the rounds in some online media, giving
unsubstantiated and false information on the incident. The Chief of Army Staff Lt Gen Tukur Yusufu Buratai has since
congratulated the troops for their swift response and urged them to
sustain the spirit.